## FAQ

### What herbs are most associated with anti-aging?

Green tea, gotu kola, turmeric, ginseng, and astragalus are among the herbs most commonly associated with healthy aging, resilience, skin support, and oxidative stress.

### What herb is best for collagen and skin aging?

Gotu kola became especially well known for connective tissue, collagen support, skin repair, and circulation.

### Why is green tea associated with longevity?

Green tea developed a longevity reputation through centuries of daily use in East Asia and modern research into antioxidant compounds like catechins.

### Do anti-aging herbs actually stop aging?

No herb stops aging, but some plants may help support healthier skin, inflammation balance, circulation, and long-term resilience.

---

Most traditional longevity herbs were never truly rare. They survived because people kept returning to them generation after generation and continued finding them useful long after fashionable remedies disappeared.

That long continuity matters more than modern marketing language ever will.
